      "author": "caasion",
      "description": "Projects can now have phases, which are independent date components with their own task task lists. This is particularly useful for projects that may span different versions or have multiple iterations. Doing so will allow all the related project information to stay within the same project instead of having to create a project for every version or iteration of something you do. \r\n\r\nOther QoL/features:\r\n- Updated styling of tracks in gantt view\r\n- Projects can now be created as project notes (or be converted manually)\r\n- Removed datepicker toggle button artifact\r\n\r\n<img width=\"882\" height=\"88\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/301820c4-18cc-44f8-b538-c8c4ae2360c0\" />\r\n<img width=\"377\" height=\"264\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e8bc3b2f-eeb3-4a40-8723-fc469fcce350\" />\r\n",
